<div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wcl1665702709004.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wcl1665702709004.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wcl1665702709004.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wcl1665702709004\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n    Global ProcScript Library </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Global ProcScript Library contains Global ProcScript objects, which are linked into\n    components at runtime when called from other ProcScript in the application. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__section_z3d_yy5_mwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1091885e51\">Characteristics</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Icon:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><img alt=\"Icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__image_v4y_zy5_mwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/library_include.png?_LANG=enus\"/></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">libprc</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"amz1665702708928.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/amz1665702708928.html\" title=\"A Global ProcScript is a Development Object that defines a ProcScript function that is linked into components at runtime when called by ProcScript in the component.\">Global ProcScript</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"srw1665702550375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/srw1665702550375.html\" title=\"A Main Development Object is a Development Object that has no parent object, is maintained using a dedicated editor, and can be saved and exported as a single unit, with all its children.\">Main Development Object</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scm1665702714238.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scm1665702714238.html\" title=\"A Library is a Main Development Object that holds a collection of objects of the same type that can be accessed or reused by other objects, either during development or at runtime.\">Library</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wcl1665702709004__table_d10742e1_d10743e1_d10744e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">libprc:<var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__section_o4q_1z5_mwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1091885e257\">Specialization</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__p_d96563e1_d96564e1_d96565e1\">Global ProcScript Library specializes Main Development\n        Object and Library in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__ul_svb_cz5_mwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wcl1665702709004__li_d39290e1_d39291e1_d39292e1\">It can only contain Global ProcScript modules. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvq1665702579531.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Global ProcScripts</a><p>Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616680\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616680\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Global ProcScript Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Global ProcScript Library A Global ProcScript Library contains Global ProcScript objects, which are linked into components at runtime when called from other ProcScript in the application. Characteristics Characteristics Icon: Object type code: libprc Main Development Object? Yes Part of: — Contains: Property , Global ProcScript Generalization: Main Development Object , Library Specializations: Compilation Output: — URI format: libprc: LibraryName Specialization Global ProcScript Library specializes Main Development Object and Library in the following ways: It can only contain Global ProcScript modules. Related Links Global ProcScripts Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}